data.description: Now with a $5000 credit towards closing costs! This is an incredibly unique home from the moment you approach the front door, passing by the grand columns and meticulously landscaped yard. You'll notice the island influence throughout the house, which has been created by the well-traveled owners. The floors have a concrete finish and the HVAC system was replaced in 2022, while the roof was replaced in 2018. It's difficult to know where to begin describing all the wonderful features! There are five bedrooms, a three-car garage, and an upgraded kitchen with stainless steel appliances, including a state-of-the-art fridge freezer and a small island. The kitchen also boasts an angled breakfast bar with pendant lighting above. All the bathrooms have been upgraded, including the floors and feature walls. Additionally, there is a laundry room with a sink, ample counter space, and cabinets for storage. The first floor of this house features two bedrooms, including the primary bedroom, which has a unique bathroom design. The second floor includes a spacious loft area and three more bedrooms. Towards the back of the house, you'll find a covered rear deck and a large fenced-in yard with a double gate for convenient access. Rather than trying to describe it all, I suggest you let the pictures speak for themselves and be sure to visit this extraordinary home.
